# Global snippets
# This file contains snippets that are always defined. I personally
# have snippets for signatures and often needed texts
# NOTE: extends from vim-snippets

# sligthly lower priority than everything else since specialized versions
# should overwrite. The user needs to adjust her priority in her snippets to
# ~-55 so that other filetypes will still overwrite.
priority -60

##########
#  Misc  #
##########
snippet copy. "copyright"
Copyright `!v &enc[:2] == "utf" ? "Â©" : "(c)"` `!v strftime("%Y")` ${1:`!v g:snips_author`}. All Rights Reserved.
endsnippet

snippet fh "File header, name author datetime description..."
Filename: ${1:`!v expand('%:t')`}
Author: ${2:`!v g:snips_about`}
Maintainer: ${3:maintainer}
Created: ${4:`!v strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M")`}
Last Upated:
         By:
Keywords: ${5:keywords}
Version: 0.1
Changelog:
    0.1 - initial version
Commentary:

${6:description}

Code:

$0
endsnippet

